<br>
How do cigarettes do good?  Well, quite frankly, if it weren't for cigarettes (and alcohol, and all our other vices), the economy of the country would virtually collapse.  The money garnered from the taxes on cancer sticks is ungodly, something Bill Gates would wet his pants to even be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> near</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  It's our way of rationalizing the sale of these disgusting little things.  If you're hooked, I'm not terribly sorry for you.  You have two choices: stop, or continue.  You knew better than to start in the first place.  But there are countless people who smoke casually, not addicted to tobacco, just imbibing it's noxious fumes occasionally to relieve stress.  The same applies for alcohol (except you drink it, not inhale fumes...).<br>
<br>
Likewise, EverQuest <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> can</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be addictive <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> in the wrong hands</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Too much EverQuest can kill you, apparently.  Too much tobacco can kill you.  Too much alcohol can kill you.  Hell, too much of ANYTHING can kill you.  Moderation is the key.  There's no two ways about that.<br>
<br>
This poor sap had mental problems, it's readily apparent.  You do NOT kill yourself over a game...there are many factors that play into suicide.  This man (if you can call him that...I mean no disrespect to him by saying this, I simply feel that most of his problems were due to a lack of maturation on his part, not fully realizing his social skills and talents...I see him as a large boy, from the interviews in the articles) never was able to grow up and face the real world.  Disappointed with his life at every turn, he found something that prolonged the inevitable suicide (I say inevitable because it would have been with or without EQ, unless someone/something intervened).  That something was EQ.<br>
<br>
Hundreds of thousands of people play EQ for what is...a GAME.  The central issue is being missed here.  This man did NOT kill himself over EQ, no matter how much his ignorant mother wishes to believe.  He killed himself because he was unhappy with his life, and he finally found something to replenish the joy life once held (EQ).  After a while, even that faded, and apparently he decided not to search for something else to fill that void.  So he did the only thing he thought to do.  He killed himself.<br>
<br>
Suicide is a coward's way out.  I admit that this man's death is a tragedy, but I refuse to feel sorry for someone without the cajones to take responsibility for his/her own life.<br>
<br>
Oh, and to Mrs. Elizabeth Woolley, the mother of this poor soul, I leave you with the only warning label you need on any video game (courtesy of the creative folks at the Safehouse):<br>
